            <title><![CDATA[This Wild Copy Of Horizon Zero Dawn Is Just Begging For Sony To Sue]]></title>
            <link>https://kotaku.com/horizon-zero-dawn-sony-light-of-motiram-tencent-copy-1851709969</link>
            <guid>https://www.resetera.com/threads/this-wild-copy-of-horizon-zero-dawn-is-just-begging-for-sony-to-sue.1047624/</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/horizon-zero-dawn-sony-light-of-motiram-tencent-copy-1851709969<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><p>As <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/nintendo-pokemon-palworld-patents-lawsuit-pocketpair-1851692965&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/nintendo-pokemon-palworld-patents-lawsuit-pocketpair-1851692965">Nintendo gears up to take down <em>Palworld</em></a></span> for its aping of <em>Pokémon</em> game design elements, another high-profile court case seems inevitable with Tencent’s announcement of <em>Light of Motiram </em>(thanks <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://www.gematsu.com/2024/11/mechanimal-open-world-survival-crafting-game-light-of-motiram-announced-for-pc&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://www.gematsu.com/2024/11/mechanimal-open-world-survival-crafting-game-light-of-motiram-announced-for-pc" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><em>Gematsu</em></a></span>), a game that looks uncannily similar to Sony’s <em>Horizon Zero Dawn</em>.</p><div><h4>Suggested Reading</h4></div><div data-video-id="195859" data-monetizable="true" data-position="sidebar" data-video-title="The Week In Games: What’s Coming Out Beyond Marvel's Spider-Man 2" data-video-blog-id="9" data-video-network="kotaku" data-video-duration="123" data-playlist="195859,196470,195896" data-current="195859"><div><p>The Week In Games: What’s Coming Out Beyond Marvel's Spider-Man 2</p></div><video disablepictureinpicture="" muted="" playsinline="" width="100%" height="100%" crossorigin="anonymous" preload="none"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/195859/195859_240p.mp4" label="240p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/195859/195859_480p.mp4" label="480p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/195859/195859_720p.mp4" label="720p" type="video/mp4"><source data-src="https://vid.kinja.com/prod/195859/195859_1080p.mp4" label="1080p" type="video/mp4"><track kind="captions" label="English" src="https://kinja.com/api/videoupload/caption/21379.vtt" srclang="en"></video><div><ul><li data-label="">Off</li><li data-label="English">English</li></ul></div></div><div><h4>Suggested Reading</h4></div><p>To be clear, we’re not saying, “Oh, hey, that kind of reminds us of <em>Horizon.</em>” This is more of a, “Oh my good lord, what are they <em>thinking</em>, this is outrageous!” <em>Light of Motiram</em> is one of those cases where you feel safe to type the words “complete rip-off” without worrying about a letter from someone’s lawyers.</p><p>It’s so hilariously blatant, that you have to wonder if it’s an exercise in attention-seeking, a deliberate troll of Sony to see if Tencent can lure a court case that the press will eagerly cover, and then pull back and change their designs once the name is in everyone’s minds. Just take a look at this screenshot, for instance:</p><figure id="" data-id="55087abab04f9d7d922409592c2f401a" data-recommend-id="image://55087abab04f9d7d922409592c2f401a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1045" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Some humans and mechanical animals look at a large tower." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Some humans and mechanical animals look at a large tower." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Tencent</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="55087abab04f9d7d922409592c2f401a" data-recommend-id="image://55087abab04f9d7d922409592c2f401a" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1045" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Some humans and mechanical animals look at a large tower." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>Yup, there’s Aloy! And those familiar robotic animals. In a post-apocalyptic world, nature taking over sci-fi architecture. And take a look at this closer view of a robot not-Aloy rides on:</p><figure id="" data-id="719167144a67164a52fbe440cc65ac67" data-recommend-id="image://719167144a67164a52fbe440cc65ac67" data-format="jpg" data-width="1421" data-height="820" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="A character sits on a mechanical steed, looking at the sun." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A character sits on a mechanical steed, looking at the sun." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Tencent</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="719167144a67164a52fbe440cc65ac67" data-recommend-id="image://719167144a67164a52fbe440cc65ac67" data-format="jpg" data-width="1421" data-height="820" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="A character sits on a mechanical steed, looking at the sun." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>For context, here’s Aloy in an official screenshot from <em>Horizon Forbidden West</em>:</p><figure id="" data-id="67a0c424668321b33013082586e11db6" data-recommend-id="image://67a0c424668321b33013082586e11db6" data-format="jpg" data-width="3101" data-height="1740" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Aloy rides a mechanical beast as she looks at the ruined remains of the Golden Gate Bridge." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Aloy rides a mechanical beast as she looks at the ruined remains of the Golden Gate Bridge." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sony</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="67a0c424668321b33013082586e11db6" data-recommend-id="image://67a0c424668321b33013082586e11db6" data-format="jpg" data-width="3101" data-height="1740" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Aloy rides a mechanical beast as she looks at the ruined remains of the Golden Gate Bridge." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>What japes!</p><p><em>Motiram</em>’s <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;External link&quot;,&quot;https://lightofmotiram.com/EN/#index&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://lightofmotiram.com/EN/#index" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official site</a></span> goes an extra step by helpfully highlighting some of its creature designs. Here’s the Agni:</p><figure id="" data-id="34e777a24a25553ed825b9459d9169cb" data-recommend-id="image://34e777a24a25553ed825b9459d9169cb" data-format="jpg" data-width="691" data-height="422" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Agni." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Agni." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Tencent</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="34e777a24a25553ed825b9459d9169cb" data-recommend-id="image://34e777a24a25553ed825b9459d9169cb" data-format="jpg" data-width="691" data-height="422" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Agni." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>And just by-the-by, here’s <em>Horizon</em>’s Fanghorn:</p><figure id="" data-id="1d9af4bbe053b06850e5cf6faa045550" data-recommend-id="image://1d9af4bbe053b06850e5cf6faa045550" data-format="jpg" data-width="1000" data-height="563" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Two Fanghorn." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Two Fanghorn." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sony</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="1d9af4bbe053b06850e5cf6faa045550" data-recommend-id="image://1d9af4bbe053b06850e5cf6faa045550" data-format="jpg" data-width="1000" data-height="563" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Two Fanghorn." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>What a coincidence!</p><p>Oh go on, you’ve been good, have another one. Here’s <em>Moratorium</em>’s (honestly, I’ve gotten bored of scrolling up to see how it’s spelt) behorned Yama:</p><figure id="" data-id="f5a4844051c419259ee21a92a160f4b6" data-recommend-id="image://f5a4844051c419259ee21a92a160f4b6" data-format="jpg" data-width="691" data-height="422" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Yama." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Yama." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Tencent</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="f5a4844051c419259ee21a92a160f4b6" data-recommend-id="image://f5a4844051c419259ee21a92a160f4b6" data-format="jpg" data-width="691" data-height="422" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Yama." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>And here’s <em>Horizon</em>’s Broadhead:</p><figure id="" data-id="c1002c6a14de10c26df2656fe9aee261" data-recommend-id="image://c1002c6a14de10c26df2656fe9aee261" data-format="jpg" data-width="742" data-height="545" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Broadhead." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Broadhead." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sony</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="c1002c6a14de10c26df2656fe9aee261" data-recommend-id="image://c1002c6a14de10c26df2656fe9aee261" data-format="jpg" data-width="742" data-height="545" data-lightbox="true" data-alt="Broadhead." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><p>I could do this all day.</p><p>This is being created by Tencent’s developer, Polaris Quest, and is of course being described as an “open-world survival crafting game,” because isn’t everything? So of course it’ll not have the epic open storyline of the wonderful <em>Horizon</em> games, but rather be yet another tree punching sim using someone else’s aesthetic. And, given that, it’ll likely be spectacularly popular, although there’s no word on a release date yet. You’ve got to assume Sony’s going to be coming for it, and fast.</p><p>Although, there’s some irony to that, given it’s Sony in Japan that’s <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/palworld-merch-plush-pokemon-nintendo-pocketpair-1851584507&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/palworld-merch-plush-pokemon-nintendo-pocketpair-1851584507">recently teamed up with <em>Palworld </em>creators Pocketpair to create a merch company</a></span>, right in the face of Nintendo’s fury.</p><p>.</p></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
